						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1461 (1539 A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>In Sanskrit verse. Registers royal gift of a pearl cuirass to the god and a jewelled crown for the goddess. Also registers a gift of 2 <hi rend="italic">kshētra</hi> of land in Saṅgamavallikā (Kūḍalūr) (vide No. 433) received from <hi rend="bold">Śrīraṅganārāyaṇa (Jīyar)</hi> by Rāmachandra for providing offerings to god Chakkarattāḻvār. <hi rend="bold">Rāmachandra</hi> is stated to be a brother of <hi rend="bold">Ahōbalapati</hi> who brought the royal gift to the temple from Sāḷuva Timma. The details of the date quoted are <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1461</hi> expressed by the chronogram <hi rend="italic">Pakshivandyē,</hi> <hi rend="bold">Viḷambi, Nakra (Makara) ba. 5, Wednesday,</hi> the Śaka year quoted is current, the details seem to correspond to <hi rend="bold">1539, A.D. January 8, Wednesday,</hi> the <hi rend="italic">tithi</hi> commenced at ·51 of the day f.d.n. ·38.</p>						

						</summary>
